  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="m">Non-static composed black-hole-field configurations are expected to exist for all types of integer-spin (bosonic) fields, see also [12]. This expectation is based on the fact that the superradiance phenomenon is a generic feature of the dynamics of all bosonic fields in rotating black-hole spacetimes</subfield>
